U.A.E.’s National Council Elections Scheduled for September

-- B y   V i v i a n   S a l a m a
-- 
2011-03-17T06:24:51Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-17/u-a-e-s-national-council-elections-scheduled-for-september.html
Elections to choose members of the
United Arab Emirates’ Federal National Council, an advisory
board to the government, will be held on Sept. 24, according to
a statement from the National Election Committee.  Half of the FNC’s 40 members are elected by a government
committee and the rest are appointed by the rulers of the
country’s seven emirates.  Winners will be announced on Sept. 28.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Vivian Salama in  Abu Dhabi  at 
 vsalama@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew J. Barden at 
 barden@bloomberg.net . 